replies.body:
I understand what Lyte is trying to do, but it isn't working. It punishes those who aren't the chronic trolls because the trolls find the easy "holes" in his thinking. The verbal abuse system doesn't work, trolls don't get banned because they troll in unbannable ways i.e. feeding, anivia walling, stealing buffs, afk, et cetera. And on top of that the trolls are the ones that more or less report people, regular everyday players say "Whatever I will never see that person again" or if they do report it is usually nulled due to the fact that they probably didn't cuss or saying anything "mean" or "troll" in game. Not to mention the broken as hell LeaverBuster is nulled when all you have to do is move every 4 minutes to prevent it from finding you so said trolls can AFK and get away with it (But then proceeds to report you for the game crashing on entry and being unable to reconnect). 

I think it's great you support Riot's decision in this, that's fine and dandy, I'm just saying it is not working as of yet; it makes more toxic players then it deals with. Unless Riot's goal is to frustrate as much of their playerbase as possible then they are very much succeeding. They are many years into this game, they should know better, they should listen better, they should learn from their mistakes, but *sigh* they just don't. {{item:3070}} 

Btw just because he has a degree in psychology doesn't make him a behavioral scientist/engineer, I have a degree in biology, biological science, and astronomy but you don't see me working for NASA or Frank Drake.
